id: ops-6p89
title: Add 'ops metrics' Prometheus exporter for pm workspace health
description: ""
type: Feature
status: closed
priority: 2
tags[4]: grafana,metrics,observability,prometheus
created_at: "2026-07-14T12:52:02.387Z"
updated_at: "2026-07-14T17:46:03.028Z"
closed_at: "2026-07-14T17:46:03.027Z"
author: claude-opus
acceptance_criteria: "ops metrics emits valid Prometheus exposition (HELP/TYPE per family, no NaN); Counts, throughput, cycle-time and backlog-age computed from real pm items; Honors global --json for the fleet routing contract (payload.repos[].path); Missing pm workspace marked unavailable without failing"
comments[3]{created_at,author,text}:
  "2026-07-14T16:46:25.196Z",claude-opus,"CI-green fixes (2026-07-14, PR #12): (1) global --json now honored via ctx.global.json — the installed CLI consumes --json into ctx.global not ctx.options, so metrics (which returns a pre-rendered Prometheus string by default) explicitly reads ctx.global; fixes the fleet routing-contract test that JSON.parsed '# HELP' text. (2) restoreCliRepoFlag now restores the FULL repeated --repos set: CLI 2026.7.14 collapses repeated flags to last-wins (not just #550 full-erasure), so the empty-only guard dropped earlier values; argv is now authoritative for CLI invocations. (3) dropped removed --isolated flag from the installed-CLI doctor test (2026.7.14 dropped it). All 41 tests pass locally."
  "2026-07-14T17:04:56.160Z",claude-opus,"Greptile P1 review round: fixed two legitimate findings against the exporter. (1) Cross-scrape cache staleness — pmItemsCache/pmAllItemsCache are module-level (dedupe within one scrape) but persisted across invocations; collectMetricsAll now clears them at the start of every scrape so a long-lived host serves fresh pm state each time. (2) Repo label collision — repoLabel returned only package.json name, so two checkouts sharing a name emitted duplicate Prometheus series; added disambiguateRepoLabels() which keeps the name as prefix and appends basename/path/#n. Added test for the collision case. 44 tests green."
  "2026-07-14T17:21:26.443Z",claude-opus,"Hardened structured stdout against a pm-CLI renderer regression. ROOT CAUSE: api.registerRenderer overrides work in pm 2026.7.6 (unwrap renderedCommandResult) but are a no-op in 2026.7.14 — 'pm ops metrics --json' double-wrapped as {pmOpsRendered,output:'...json...'}, hiding payload.repos from 'jq .repos' (sibling ops commands were unaffected since they return bare objects for the global --json path). FIX: metrics now returns the BARE result object for json/toon stdout (defers to the CLI global renderer, like siblings); --output file still serializes/writes itself; prometheus --output still emits clean raw exposition. Verified clean+unwrapped under BOTH pm 2026.7.6 and 2026.7.14. Filing a pm-cli issue for the registerRenderer regression."
close_reason: "Delivered: 'pm ops metrics' Prometheus exporter merged via PR #12 (squash 79eb2c6). All Greptile P1s fixed across 3 review rounds (cache staleness, repo-label collision-proofing, --json bare-object routing for the CLI renderer regression pm-cli#560), cubic maintainability refactor (unified readPmItemList). 45 tests green. Verified with real fleet data under pm 2026.7.6 and 2026.7.14; --output textfile emits clean node_exporter exposition."
body: "Add an 'ops metrics' command that renders pm workspace health as Prometheus text-format gauges so the existing Prometheus/Grafana stack can scrape fleet project-management signals. Per-repo series: pm_items{status}, pm_active_items_by_type, pm_active_items_by_priority, pm_blocked_items (via pm list-blocked), pm_stale_items (--stale-days, default 14), pm_throughput_items{window=7d|30d}, pm_cycle_time_seconds{quantile} and pm_backlog_age_seconds{quantile} derived from created_at/closed_at (same closed_at methodology as pm-brief momentum), pm_workspace_available, pm_repos_scanned, pm_scrape_duration_seconds. Default output is Prometheus exposition; --output writes a node_exporter textfile; --json/--format json exposes the structured routing contract. Reframe of companion feature pm-cli-website-e8ty (enrich existing pm-ops over a standalone pm-metrics package)."
